  "text": "Proof. A key observation is that each point of [CITATION_1] 4 lies on an even number of these lines. The point (1, 2, 3, 4) lies on the 4 lines of length 1, and no other. Take any other point (x 1 , x 2 , x 3 , x 4 ) expressible as ℓ j (x) for some index j and some x ∈ {1, 2, 3, 4}. Any coordinate i where x i = i must be a variable coordinate of ℓ j ; any coordinate i where x i = i = x must be a constant coordinate of ℓ j . There is always exactly one coordinate where x i = i = x, so there are 2 choices for j, depending on whether that coordinate is variable or constant. If [CITATION_2] 4 is 2-colored, choose either of the colors, and add up the number of points of that color on each of the fifteen lines. This total must be even, because each point is counted an even number of times. However, 15 odd numbers cannot add up to an even total, so one of the lines must contribute an even number. Therefore not all 15 lines can be odd.",
